16 (b) Hold all social security benefit payments received on behalf of
17 a child beneficiary separate and apart from the department's funds, and
18 except as provided in subdivision (5)(c) of this section, in a trust
19 account established and maintained for the child beneficiary;
20 (c) Manage such benefit payments in a manner that avoids exceeding
21 the federal social security asset and resource limits, including holding
22 benefit payments in the established trust account and in accounts and
23 programs not counted toward such limits, so as to conserve funds without
24 exceeding such limits. Such accounts and programs include, but are not
25 limited to, (i) a plan for achieving self-support as described in section
26 68-1007, (ii) an achieving a better life experience account as described
27 in sections 77-1401 to 77-1409, (iii) an individual development account
28 as described in 45 C.F.R. 263.20, (iv) a special-needs trust as defined
29 in section 30-4513, and (v) a dedicated account for social security back
30 payments;
31 (d) Conserve a minimum amount of social security benefit payments
